{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_123","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented the shared wave-planning extension in [simulation_planning.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/simulation_planning.py). `resolve_manifest_simulation_plan()` now normalizes `surface_wave` arms through the same manifest path as baseline arms, adds explicit `surface_wave_execution_plan` data, records operator and coupling inventories, derives deterministic model/operator identities for run hashing, and resolves a conservative spectral substep schedule plus timestep guardrails instead of leaving wave runners to interpret manifests ad hoc.\n\nThe surface-wave contract additions in [surface_wave_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/surface_wave_contract.py), [surface_wave_model_design.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/docs/surface_wave_model_design.md), [pipeline_notes.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/docs/pipeline_notes.md), and [__init__.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/__init__.py) remain in place and are now exercised by planning. I also updated the planning and workflow fixtures in [test_simulation_planning.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_simulation_planning.py), [test_simulator_execution.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_simulator_execution.py), and [milestone9_readiness.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/milestone9_readiness.py) so wave arms validate against real local operator metadata instead of placeholder manifests. New regression coverage in [test_simulation_planning.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/persona